Open city data is critical for smart cities and is becoming increasingly available, thanks to open government initiatives. Yet, we still know little about the needs of users concerning open data reuse. Taking fragmented and scattered issues reported by users in several works as a starting point, this article formulates user needs statements for research at the intersection of the topics of web, city, and data reuse. The 27 user needs statements proposed can inform the design and evaluation of tools that facilitate open data reuse.